# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Same-origin proxy for the API + WebSocket. Without this, the SPA at
# rmpgutah.us would have to call https://api.rmpgutah.us/api/* directly
# (cross-origin), which means every request must pass connect-src CSP
# check against api.rmpgutah.us. The zone-level Cloudflare Transform Rule
# that injects the production CSP has, in the past, silently dropped that
# origin from connect-src — instantly breaking every API call from the
# SPA. Routing /api/* through Pages as a 200-proxy keeps requests
# same-origin so connect-src 'self' is sufficient regardless of what the
# Transform Rule looks like.
#
# Status 200 = transparent proxy (browser sees rmpgutah.us as origin).
# :splat captures everything after /api/ and is appended to the target.

/api/*  https://api.rmpgutah.us/api/:splat  200

# SPA fallback — every non-asset, non-API path serves index.html so the
# React Router can handle the route client-side.
/*  /index.html  200
